    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-06-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-06-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="563" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d563">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Carlos Ezeta</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-06-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I implore your Government not to deliver my brother, Antonio, to the
                            rebels of Salvador, who are only interested in assassinating him.
                            Whatever promises they make I assure you they will kill him; all are
                            personal enemies. In 1890 Ezeta conquered, captured them, and spared
                            their lives. My brother could have taken another steamer, but believed
                            he would have more protection under the starry flag of the great
                            Republic. Is it possible that this is not so? Please reply.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
